'''Hul Jharkhand Party''', a [[political party]] in [[India]]. Founded by Justin Richard on December 28, 1968, after the fragmentation of the [[Jharkhand Party]]. The party worked amongst the [[Santhal people|Santhal]] populations. It demanded a separate tribal-majority state and social reform. A splinter group, the [[Bihar Progressive Hul Jharkhand Party]] was later founded by [[Sibu Soren]].

