A Two-member Viceroy's Executive Council (composed of Sir [[Henry Maine]] and Sir [[James Fitzjames Stephen]]) also worked on the side-lines of the Law Commissions and ensured the passage of the following noteworthy laws;<ref>{{Cite book | author=Riddick, John A. | authorlink= | title=The history of British India: a chronology | year=2006 | publisher=Praeger | location=Westport, Conn. | isbn=0-313-32280-5 | pages=}}</ref>
