===Nineteenth Law Commission=== The nineteenth Law Commission of India's Chairman was Chairman Mr. Justice P. V. Reddi, 2009-2012 of 19th Law Comiission.<ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/PV-Reddy-to-head-Law-Commission/Article1-521234.aspx Hindustantimes.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111012131514/http://www.hindustantimes.com/PV-Reddy-to-head-Law-Commission/Article1-521234.aspx |date=12 October 2011 }}</ref> {| class="wikitable" |- ! Report No. ! Presented in ! Title of Report |- | 235 | <center> 2010 </center> | Conversion/reconversion to another religion - mode of proof |- | 236 | <center> 2010 </center> | Court-fees in Supreme Court vis-à-vis Corporate Litigation |- | 237 | <center> 2011 </center> | Compounding of (IPC) offences |- | 238 | <center> 2011 </center> | Amendment of Section 89 of the [[Civil Procedure Code, 1908|Code of Civil Procedure, 1908]] and Allied provisions |- | 239 | <center> 2012 </center> | Expeditious Investigation and Trial of Criminal Cases Against 2012 Influential Public Personalities |- | 240 | <center> 2012 </center> | Costs in Civil Litigation |- | 241 | <center> 2012 </center> | Passive Euthanasia - A Relook
