The '''Promissory Oaths Act 1871''' (34 & 35 Vict c 48) is an [[Acts of Parliament in the United Kingdom|Act]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]].
It was passed with a view to the [[statute law revision|revision of the statute law]], and particularly to the preparation of the [[revised edition of the statutes]] then in progress.<ref>The Promissory Oaths Act 1871, preamble</ref>
