{{Politics of Tajikistan}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Tajikistan]] on 22 June 2003. The changes included removing Article 65, which limited the President to a single term of office.<ref>[http://www.electionguide.org/election.php?ID=366 Overview] IFES</ref> They were approved by 94% of voters, with a turnout of 96%.<ref>[http://www.irinnews.org/PrintReport.aspx?ReportID=20195 TAJIKISTAN: Focus on constitutional referendum] IRIN, 26 June 2003</ref>
