{{Infobox treaty | name = Treaty of Maastricht | long_name = | image = | image_width = | image_alt = | caption = | type = bilateral treaty | context = | date_drafted = | date_signed = {{Start date|df=yes|1843|8|8}} | location_signed = [[Maastricht]], [[Netherlands]] | date_sealed = | date_effective = | condition_effective = | date_expiration = | date_expiry = | mediators = | negotiators = | original_signatories = Belgium, Netherlands | signatories = | parties = | ratifiers = Belgium, Netherlands | depositor = | depositories = | citations = | language = | languages = | wikisource = | wikisource1 = | footnotes = }} {{Refimprove|date=September 2014}}The '''Treaty of Maastricht''', signed in 1843 by [[Belgium]] and the [[Netherlands]], established the border between the two countries. It resulted in a very [[Baarle-Hertog|complicated frontier]] in parts that passes through houses and has tiny enclaves<ref name="flickr">{{cite web|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/amapple/5875576341/|title=Flickr - Photo Sharing!|publisher=flickr.com|accessdate=21 August 2015}}</ref> due to land ownership dating back to the 12th century.<ref>http://www.baarledigitaal.org/historie/ontstaan_baarlehertog_en_baarlenassau.php</ref>
Part of the left bank of the [[Meuse (river)|Meuse]], near Maastricht, came back to the Netherlands.<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Belgique DE L'EST|author=DOMINIQUE, AL|date=2008|publisher=PETIT FUTE|isbn=9782746922136|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=5jdzeiIQZZkC&pg=PA91|page=91|accessdate=21 August 2015}}</ref>
This treaty was signed four years after the [[Treaty of London (1839)|Treaty of London]].
